Newdataframe for GWR

point_sd <- extract(
  pca_sandiengo,
  sandiengo %>% as('Spatial'),
  sp = TRUE)

Selections of the best bandwidht

bw1 <- gwr.sel(
  formula = pc1 ~ pc2,
  data = point_sd@data,
  coords = coordinates(point_sd),
  adapt = TRUE,
  longlat = TRUE

GWR Model

mod_pc12 <- gwr(
  formula = pc1 ~ pc2,
  data = point_sd@data,
  coords = coordinates(point_sd),
  bandwidth = bw1
  ) 

mod_pc13 <- gwr(
  formula = pc1 ~ pc3,
  data = point_sd@data,
  coords = coordinates(point_sd),
  bandwidth = bw2
)

mod_pc23 <- gwr(
  formula = pc2 ~ pc3,
  data = point_sd@data,
  coords = coordinates(point_sd),
  bandwidth = bw3
)

intcp12 <- mod_pc12$SDF[2] %>% st_as_sf()
intcp13 <- mod_pc13$SDF[2] %>% st_as_sf()
intcp23 <-mod_pc23$SDF[2] %>% st_as_sf()

point to polygon

point_to_grid <- qgis_function('native:joinattributesbylocation')
new_sd12 <- point_to_grid(
  INPUT = region,
  JOIN = intcp12,
  PREDICATE =1,
  .quiet = TRUE,
  OUTPUT = qgis_tmp_vector()
) %>% 
  qgis_output('OUTPUT') %>% 
  st_read() %>% 
  rename(slope = `X.Intercept.`)

Maps

p1 <- new_sd12 %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill = slope)) +
  geom_sf(color = 'white',lwd = 0.1) + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  scale_fill_viridis_c(option = 'magma') +
  theme(
    axis.title.x = element_text(
      size = 12,
      face = 'bold',
      family = 'Roboto Slab'),
    axis.title.y = element_text(
      size = 12,
      face = 'bold',
      family = 'Roboto Slab'
    ),
    title =  element_text(
      size = 12,
      face = 'bold',
      family = 'Roboto Slab' )
  ) + 
  labs(title = 'PC1 ~ PC2, Intercept of PC2')
